{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_015G2bopvFGYBAwsRPdH6oPq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017o5AzsjRCLiaPTx5Nrg5h4","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Store & State Engineer","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"You are the Store & State Engineer for miniflow — a minimal workflow execution engine.\n\n## Working Directory\n/Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow\n\n## What Already Exists\n- go.mod (module miniflow)\n- internal/model/workflow.go — Workflow, ActivitySpec, WorkflowDefinition structs\n- internal/model/run.go — WorkflowRun, ActivityRun structs, Status constants (StatusPending, StatusRunning, StatusCompleted, StatusFailed, StatusCancelled)\n- internal/model/event.go — Event struct, EventType constants\n\nThe model types use standard Go time.Time fields. WorkflowRun and ActivityRun use *time.Time for nullable timestamp fields (StartedAt, CompletedAt, LastHeartbeat).\n\n## Tech Stack\n- Go 1.22+, standard library\n- modernc.org/sqlite (pure Go, no CGO)\n- google/uuid for IDs\n\n## Your Tasks\n\n### Task 1: Implement SQLite store\nCreate internal/store/store.go with:\n- `NewStore(dsn string) (*Store, error)` — opens SQLite DB, creates all 4 tables + indexes, returns Store\n- Tables (use these exact schemas):\n  ```sql\n  CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS workflows (\n    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n    name TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,\n    definition TEXT NOT NULL,\n    created_at DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP\n  );\n  CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS workflow_runs (\n    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n    workflow_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES workflows(id),\n    status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',\n    input TEXT DEFAULT '{}',\n    output TEXT DEFAULT '',\n    current_step INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n    started_at DATETIME,\n    completed_at DATETIME,\n    created_at DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP\n  );\n  CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS activity_runs (\n    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n    workflow_run_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES workflow_runs(id),\n    activity_name TEXT NOT NULL,\n    step_index INTEGER NOT NULL,\n    status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',\n    input TEXT DEFAULT '{}',\n    output TEXT DEFAULT '',\n    attempts INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n    max_retries INTEGER DEFAULT 3,\n    timeout_seconds INTEGER DEFAULT 30,\n    started_at DATETIME,\n    completed_at DATETIME,\n    last_heartbeat DATETIME,\n    created_at DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP\n  );\n  CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS events (\n    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n    workflow_run_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES workflow_runs(id),\n    activity_run_id TEXT,\n    event_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n    payload TEXT DEFAULT '{}',\n    created_at DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP\n  );\n  ```\n- Methods:\n  - CreateWorkflow(w *model.Workflow) error\n  - GetWorkflow(id string) (*model.Workflow, error)\n  - GetWorkflowByName(name string) (*model.Workflow, error)\n  - ListWorkflows() ([]model.Workflow, error)\n  - CreateRun(r *model.WorkflowRun) error\n  - GetRun(id string) (*model.WorkflowRun, error)\n  - ListRuns(status string, limit int) ([]model.WorkflowRun, error)\n  - UpdateRun(r *model.WorkflowRun) error\n  - CreateActivityRun(ar *model.ActivityRun) error\n  - GetActivityRun(id string) (*model.ActivityRun, error)\n  - GetActivityRunsByRunID(runID string) ([]model.ActivityRun, error)\n  - UpdateActivityRun(ar *model.ActivityRun) error\n  - ClaimNextActivity() (*model.ActivityRun, error) — atomically find oldest pending activity_run and set status=running, started_at=now. Return nil,nil if none found.\n  - AppendEvent(e *model.Event) error\n  - ListEvents(runID string) ([]model.Event, error)\n  - Stats() (map[string]int, error) — counts of workflow_runs grouped by status\n  - Close() error\n\nFor ClaimNextActivity, use a transaction: SELECT the oldest pending activity_run (ORDER BY created_at ASC LIMIT 1), UPDATE it to running status with started_at = now, then return it.\n\nFor GetWorkflow/GetRun/GetActivityRun, return ErrNotFound if no row found.\n\nStore the WorkflowDefinition as JSON in the definition column (marshal on create, unmarshal on get).\n\nHandle nullable time fields with sql.NullTime or similar approach.\n\n### Task 2: Create store errors\nCreate internal/store/errors.go with:\n- ErrNotFound\n- ErrDuplicateWorkflow (for UNIQUE constraint on workflow name)\n\n### Task 3: Write store tests\nCreate internal/store/store_test.go using `:memory:` SQLite:\n- TestCreateAndGetWorkflow\n- TestListWorkflows\n- TestDuplicateWorkflow (should return ErrDuplicateWorkflow)\n- TestCreateAndGetRun\n- TestListRuns with status filter\n- TestUpdateRun\n- TestCreateAndGetActivityRun\n- TestUpdateActivityRun\n- TestClaimNextActivity (test that it claims oldest pending, returns nil when none)\n- TestClaimNextActivityConcurrency (use goroutines to verify no double-claim)\n- TestAppendAndListEvents\n- TestStats\n- TestGetWorkflowNotFound (should return ErrNotFound)\n\nAfter writing all files, run: `cd /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow && go mod tidy && go test ./internal/store/... -v`\n\nFix any issues until tests pass. This is critical — the store is the foundation for everything else.","run_in_background":true},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":225,"cache_read_input_tokens":26196,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":225},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"60911857-bac5-4e5c-815c-3e677cf891bd","uuid":"fdc9c0ce-1bc0-4f2c-9ce3-55d476af8697"}
