{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MY3iZkT2jVvLeAdDiLidJG","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Async agent launched successfully.\nagentId: a9f1702e430b40d12 (internal ID - do not mention to user. Use to resume later if needed.)\nThe agent is working in the background. You will be notified automatically when it completes.\nDo not duplicate this agent's work — avoid working with the same files or topics it is using. Work on non-overlapping tasks, or briefly tell the user what you launched and end your response.\noutput_file: /private/tmp/claude-504/-Users-michaelhabib-dev-teams-sbx-agent-orchestra-examples-miniflow/tasks/a9f1702e430b40d12.output\nIf asked, you can check progress before completion by using Read or Bash tail on the output file."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"60911857-bac5-4e5c-815c-3e677cf891bd","uuid":"a1a5cc0c-37dd-4be6-9b29-8a070a745fae","tool_use_result":{"isAsync":true,"status":"async_launched","agentId":"a9f1702e430b40d12","description":"Scheduler & Executor Engineer","prompt":"You are the Scheduler & Executor Engineer for miniflow — a minimal workflow execution engine.\n\n## Working Directory\n/Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow\n\n## What Already Exists\n- go.mod (module miniflow)\n- internal/model/workflow.go — Workflow, ActivitySpec, WorkflowDefinition structs\n- internal/model/run.go — WorkflowRun, ActivityRun structs, Status constants (StatusPending, StatusRunning, StatusCompleted, StatusFailed, StatusCancelled)\n- internal/model/event.go — Event struct, EventType constants (EventWorkflowStarted, EventWorkflowCompleted, EventWorkflowFailed, EventWorkflowCancelled, EventActivityScheduled, EventActivityStarted, EventActivityCompleted, EventActivityFailed, EventActivityRetried, EventActivityTimedOut, EventActivityHeartbeat)\n\n## Tech Stack\n- Go 1.22+, standard library\n- modernc.org/sqlite (pure Go, no CGO)\n- google/uuid for IDs\n\n## Important: Store Interface\nThe Store & State Engineer is building the actual SQLite store concurrently. You should define a store interface that your executor/scheduler depends on, so you can test with a mock. The real store will implement this interface.\n\nDefine the interface in your executor package with the methods you need:\n\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n    GetRun(id string) (*model.WorkflowRun, error)\n    UpdateRun(r *model.WorkflowRun) error\n    GetWorkflow(id string) (*model.Workflow, error)\n    CreateActivityRun(ar *model.ActivityRun) error\n    GetActivityRunsByRunID(runID string) ([]model.ActivityRun, error)\n    AppendEvent(e *model.Event) error\n    ListRuns(status string, limit int) ([]model.WorkflowRun, error)\n}\n```\n\n## Your Tasks\n\n### Task 1: Implement workflow executor\nCreate internal/executor/executor.go:\n\n```go\ntype Executor struct {\n    store RunStore\n}\n\nfunc NewExecutor(store RunStore) *Executor\n```\n\nKey method: `AdvanceRun(runID string) error`\n1. Get the workflow run\n2. Get the workflow definition\n3. Get all activity runs for this workflow run\n4. Check current step's activity run status:\n   - If no activity run exists for current step → create one (schedule it) with resolved input\n   - If current activity is completed → advance current_step, create next activity or mark run completed\n   - If current activity is failed (attempts >= max_retries) → mark run failed\n   - If current activity is running or pending → do nothing (wait)\n5. Append appropriate events for each state change\n\nInput expression resolver (`resolveInputExpr`):\n- `$.input` → return the workflow run's input\n- `$.steps[N].output` → return the Nth activity run's output (by step_index)\n- Empty string or anything else → return the workflow run's input as default\n\nAlso implement: `StartRun(runID string) error` — sets run status to running, sets started_at, appends workflow_started event, then calls AdvanceRun.\n\nAlso implement: `CancelRun(runID string) error` — sets run status to cancelled, sets completed_at, appends workflow_cancelled event.\n\n### Task 2: Implement scheduler\nCreate internal/executor/scheduler.go:\n\n```go\ntype Scheduler struct {\n    executor *Executor\n    store    RunStore\n    interval time.Duration\n    quit     chan struct{}\n}\n\nfunc NewScheduler(executor *Executor, store RunStore, interval time.Duration) *Scheduler\nfunc (s *Scheduler) Start()  // starts polling in a goroutine\nfunc (s *Scheduler) Stop()   // signals quit and returns\n```\n\nThe scheduler polls on interval:\n1. List all \"pending\" runs → call executor.StartRun for each\n2. List all \"running\" runs → call executor.AdvanceRun for each\n3. Log errors but don't crash\n\n### Task 3: Write executor tests\nCreate internal/executor/executor_test.go with a mock store implementation:\n\n- TestAdvanceRun_SchedulesFirstActivity: new run with no activity runs → creates first activity\n- TestAdvanceRun_AdvancesToNextStep: current activity completed → creates next activity, increments step\n- TestAdvanceRun_CompletesWorkflow: last activity completed → marks run completed\n- TestAdvanceRun_FailsWorkflow: activity failed with max retries exhausted → marks run failed\n- TestResolveInputExpr: test $.input and $.steps[N].output resolution\n- TestStartRun: sets status to running and advances\n\nUse a mock store (struct implementing RunStore with maps/slices) for testing.\n\nAfter writing all files, run: `cd /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow && go mod tidy && go test ./internal/executor/... -v`\n\nFix any issues until tests pass.","outputFile":"/private/tmp/claude-504/-Users-michaelhabib-dev-teams-sbx-agent-orchestra-examples-miniflow/tasks/a9f1702e430b40d12.output","canReadOutputFile":true}}
