{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_015G2bopvFGYBAwsRPdH6oPq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QEkmo18GUgeWtwq6xiKttA","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Activity Runtime Engineer","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"You are the Activity Runtime Engineer for miniflow — a minimal workflow execution engine.\n\n## Working Directory\n/Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow\n\n## What Already Exists\n- go.mod (module miniflow)\n- internal/model/workflow.go — Workflow, ActivitySpec, WorkflowDefinition structs\n- internal/model/run.go — WorkflowRun, ActivityRun structs, Status constants (StatusPending, StatusRunning, StatusCompleted, StatusFailed, StatusCancelled)\n- internal/model/event.go — Event struct, EventType constants (EventActivityScheduled, EventActivityStarted, EventActivityCompleted, EventActivityFailed, EventActivityRetried, EventActivityTimedOut, EventActivityHeartbeat)\n\n## Tech Stack\n- Go 1.22+, standard library\n- google/uuid for IDs\n\n## Your Tasks\n\n### Task 1: Implement activity registry\nCreate internal/activity/registry.go:\n\n```go\n// HandlerFunc is the signature for activity handlers.\ntype HandlerFunc func(ctx context.Context, input string) (string, error)\n\n// Registry holds registered activity handlers.\ntype Registry struct {\n    mu       sync.RWMutex\n    handlers map[string]HandlerFunc\n}\n\nfunc NewRegistry() *Registry\nfunc (r *Registry) Register(name string, handler HandlerFunc)\nfunc (r *Registry) Execute(ctx context.Context, name string, input string) (string, error)\n```\n\nExecute should return an error if the activity type is not registered.\n\n### Task 2: Implement built-in activity handlers\nCreate internal/activity/builtin.go:\n\n```go\nfunc RegisterBuiltins(r *Registry)\n```\n\nBuilt-in handlers:\n- **noop**: return input as-is\n- **sleep**: parse `{\"duration_ms\": N}` from input, sleep for that duration (respect ctx cancellation), return `{\"slept\": N}`\n- **http-call**: parse `{\"url\": \"...\", \"method\": \"GET|POST\", \"body\": \"...\"}` from input, make HTTP request, return `{\"status\": N, \"body\": \"...\"}`. Default method to GET. Respect ctx for timeout.\n- **log**: parse `{\"message\": \"...\"}` from input, log.Printf it, return `{\"logged\": true}`\n- **fail**: always return an error `errors.New(\"activity failed\")` (for testing retries)\n\n### Task 3: Implement activity worker pool\nCreate internal/activity/worker.go:\n\nDefine the store interface the worker needs:\n\n```go\ntype ActivityStore interface {\n    ClaimNextActivity() (*model.ActivityRun, error)\n    UpdateActivityRun(ar *model.ActivityRun) error\n    AppendEvent(e *model.Event) error\n}\n```\n\nWorker pool:\n\n```go\ntype WorkerPool struct {\n    store    ActivityStore\n    registry *Registry\n    count    int\n    interval time.Duration\n    quit     chan struct{}\n}\n\nfunc NewWorkerPool(store ActivityStore, registry *Registry, count int, interval time.Duration) *WorkerPool\nfunc (wp *WorkerPool) Start()  // starts 'count' goroutines, each polling for activities\nfunc (wp *WorkerPool) Stop()   // signals quit, waits for workers to finish\n```\n\nEach worker loop:\n1. ClaimNextActivity from store\n2. If nil, sleep for interval and retry\n3. If claimed:\n   - Set up context with timeout (activity's timeout_seconds)\n   - Append activity_started event\n   - Execute via registry\n   - On success: set status=completed, output=result, completed_at=now, append activity_completed event\n   - On failure: increment attempts. If attempts >= max_retries: set status=failed, append activity_failed event. Else: set status=pending (for retry), append activity_retried event.\n   - On context timeout: set status=pending for retry or failed if exhausted, append activity_timed_out event\n4. Start a heartbeat goroutine while executing: every 5 seconds update last_heartbeat on the activity_run and append activity_heartbeat event. Stop when execution completes.\n\n### Task 4: Write worker tests\nCreate internal/activity/worker_test.go:\n\nCreate a mock ActivityStore for testing.\n\nTests:\n- TestRegistry_ExecuteUnknown: executing unregistered activity returns error\n- TestBuiltinNoop: noop returns input\n- TestBuiltinSleep: sleep works and returns {\"slept\": N}\n- TestBuiltinLog: log returns {\"logged\": true}\n- TestBuiltinFail: fail returns error\n- TestWorkerSuccessfulExecution: worker claims activity, executes successfully, updates status to completed\n- TestWorkerFailureAndRetry: worker claims activity that fails, checks it's set back to pending with incremented attempts\n- TestWorkerMaxRetriesExhausted: activity at max retries fails → status set to failed\n\nFor worker tests, you can start a single-worker pool, seed the mock store with an activity run, and verify the store state after a short sleep.\n\nAfter writing all files, run: `cd /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow && go mod tidy && go test ./internal/activity/... -v`\n\nFix any issues until tests pass.","run_in_background":true},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":225,"cache_read_input_tokens":26196,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":225},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"60911857-bac5-4e5c-815c-3e677cf891bd","uuid":"3ee0d726-582d-439e-9b48-0a46646b9551"}
